SOSHANGUVE - Gauteng Premier David Makhura joined mourners at the funeral of five Soshanguve children crushed by a falling light fitting in a freak accident. Family, friends, politicians and community members gathered at a local community hall to remember them. Several speakers also called on the authorities to address infrastructure problems and prevent such incidents. The City of Tshwane said a preliminary probe showed that cable theft was to blame. Makhura said someone had to take responsibility for the incident. He said that wherever he has authority, he ensures people are held accountable.  Friends of the children who were killed performed a short musical item to comfort mourners during the funeral. African News Agency